ompPotential\":4,\n    \"growthPotential\":6,\n    \"riskScore\":5,\n    \"verdict\":\"MAYBE\",\n    \"summary\":\"Healthcare staffing marketplace for facilities and clinicians.\",\n    \"whyFit\":\"Operationally feasible but likely under-leverages your systems-builder ceiling.\",\n    \"reviewSummary\":\"Fast-paced support environment signals; growth stage intensity.\",\n    \"riskFlags\":[\"Support-heavy role\",\"Lower strategic scope\"],\n    \"approach\":\"Only pursue as bridge role if immediate stability needed.\",\n    \"website\":\"https://www.clipboardhealth.com\",\n    \"linkedin\":\"https://www.linkedin.com/company/clipboard-health/\",\n    \"jobPosting\":\"\",\n    \"reviews\":\"https://www.google.com/search?q=Clipboard+Health+reviews\"\n  }\n]\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773105429741}}
{"type":"message","id":"4721f77c","parentId":"8a0030b7","timestamp":"2026-03-10T01:17:27.240Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summary of QA inspection for Company Intel Dashboard V3:\n\n1. Dashboard Files and Structure:\n- index.html: Basic valid HTML structure but references \"styles.css\" and \"app.js\" which do not exist by those exact names. Actual files appear to be \"style.css\" (missing) and \"script.js\" respectively. This will break styling and script functionality.\n- style.css file is missing entirely from the target folder. This is a critical issue as the dashboard will render unstyled.\n- script.js is present but appears to be an earlier version with older variable names and mismatched element IDs compared to index.html. E.g. index.html uses \"q\" input and \"verdictFilter\" select, but script.js uses \"search\" and \"decisionFilter\". This mismatch breaks filtering UI functionality.\n\n2. Data File Validation:\n- companies.v3.json contains company objects with expected fields, but field names mismatch script expectations:\n  - JSON uses \"verdict\" field but script uses \"decision\"\n  - JSON uses \"riskScore\" but script uses \"risk\"\n- Links and URLs in companies.v3.json appear valid.\n- Some fields used by script like pros, cons, tasks are not present in JSON data.\n\n3. Script Logic Issues:\n- The filtering logic uses element IDs that do not match index.html, causing UI controls to break.\n- The field names accessed from companies array are inconsistent with the JSON fields.\n- Stats calculation uses \"decision\" but JSON has \"verdict\".\n- Task toggling and note saving logic expect tasks to be present which JSON doesn't have, potentially causing errors.\n\n4. Recommendations / Fixes:\n- Update index.html to point to \"style.css\" and \"script.js\" instead of \"styles.css\" and \"app.js\".\n- Add or restore missing style.css file or rename as needed.\n- Align script.js element selectors with index.html IDs (\"q\" and \"verdictFilter\").\n- Align script.js data field names with JSON (\"verdict\" instead of \"decision\", \"riskScore\" instead of \"risk\").\n- Add default empty tasks, pros, and cons fields to companies object in script or JSON to prevent errors.\n- Review verdict/scoring logic but JSON verdicts (GO, MAYBE, SKIP) appear consistent; scores look plausible.\n\n5. Pass/Fail Recommendation:\n- Currently, critical structural and naming mismatches prevent dashboard from functioning.\n- After applying fixes above, it should be operational and reliable for morning run.\n- Therefore: Fail now, but ready to pass with fixes applied.\n\nI will now create the QA report file with these findings and recommendations.","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02c22ab212ee4de40069af7116ea20819f966313c264d0a0b1\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_bfQLrZzS3hF5h6oXpT17XdXL|fc_02c22ab212ee4de40069af7120b760819f84f99c87a6cc1842","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"OpenClawMissionControl/dashboard/company-intel-v3/QA_REPORT_KELLY.md","content":"# QA Report for Company Intel Dashboard V3\n\n## Critical Issues\n- index.html references missing styles.css instead of style.css. No style.css file found. Dashboard will render unstyled.\n- index.html references app.js but actual script file is script.js. This breaks script loading.\n- script.js uses incorrect element IDs (`search` and `decisionFilter`) which do not match index.html IDs (`q` and `verdictFilter`). UI filtering controls broken.\n- Field names inconsistent between companies.v3.json and script.js (`verdict` vs `decision`, `riskScore` vs `risk`).\n- companies.v3.json lacks some fields (tasks, pros, cons) expected by script, may cause runtime errors.\n\n## Medium Issues\n- LocalStorage saving and task toggling features depend on presence of tasks data which JSON currently lacks.\n- Some HTML content (role, fit scores) relies on exact field mappings; inconsistent names increase maintenance risk.\n\n## Quick Wins\n- Rename references in index.html: change styles.css → style.css and app.js → script.js.\n- Update script.js to use correct element IDs: `q` and `verdictFilter`.\n- Update script.js to use JSON field names: `verdict` (instead of `decision`), `riskScore` (instead of `risk`).\n- Add default empty arrays for tasks, pros, and cons in script to avoid errors.\n\n## Pass/Fail Recommendation\n- Fail in current state due to critical file and naming mismatches.\n- Pass after fixes applied as above, ensuring alignment between HTML, script, and JSON data.\n\n---\n\nThis concludes QA for the overnight build. Please apply fixes for stability and usability in morning run.\n"},"partialJson":"{\"path\":\"OpenClawMissionControl/dashboard/company-intel-v3/QA_REPORT_KELLY.md\",\"content\":\"# QA Report for Company Intel Dashboard V3\\n\\n## Critical Issues\\n- index.html references missing styles.css instead of style.css. No style.css file found. Dashboard will render unstyled.\\n- index.html references app.js but actual script file is script.js. This breaks script loading.\\n- script.js uses incorrect element IDs (`search` and `decisionFilter`) which do not match index.html IDs (`q` and `verdictFilter`). UI filtering controls broken.\\n- Field names inconsistent between companies.v3.json and script.js (`verdict` vs `decision`, `riskScore` vs `risk`).\\n- companies.v3.json lacks some fields (tasks, pros, cons) expected by script, may cause runtime errors.\\n\\n## Medium Issues\\n- LocalStorage saving and task toggling features depend on presence of tasks data which JSON currently lacks.\\n- Some HTML content (role, fit scores) relies on exact field mappings; inconsistent names increase maintenance risk.\\n\\n## Quick Wins\\n- Rename references in index.html: change styles.css → style.css and app.js → script.js.\\n- Update script.js to use correct element IDs: `q` and `verdictFilter`.\\n- Update script.js to use JSON field names: `verdict` (instead of `decision`), `riskScore` (instead of `risk`).\\n- Add default empty arrays for tasks, pros, and cons in script to avoid errors.\\n\\n## Pass/Fail Recommendation\\n- Fail in current state due to critical file and naming mismatches.\\n- Pass after fixes applied as above, ensuring alignment between HTML, script, and JSON data.\\n\\n---\\n\\nThis concludes QA for the overnight build. Please apply fixes for stability and usability in morning run.\\n\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-4.1-mini","usage":{"input":3364,"output":531,"cacheRead":8064,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":11959,"cost":{"input":0.0013456000000000002,"output":0.0008496,"cacheRead":0.0008064000000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0030016000000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773105429743}}
